description:
Add pixelated/bitmap aesthetic to the retro terminal UI in app/frontend/src/index.css:

1. Add image-rendering properties for pixelated graphics:
   - image-rendering: pixelated;
   - image-rendering: -moz-crisp-edges;
   - image-rendering: crisp-edges;

2. Consider adding subtle pixelation effects:
   - Apply to images, icons, or specific UI elements
   - Could use CSS filters or backdrop effects

3. Optionally adjust font rendering for more bitmap-like appearance:
   - font-smooth: never;
   - -webkit-font-smoothing: none;
   - -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;

4. Keep the retro terminal aesthetic intact (monospace fonts, #FFB633 accent, dark theme)

Target: app/frontend/src/index.css and any component files if needed for specific pixelated elements.

